Wash your hands frequently, This is very important. The virus can live on your hands only up to five to 10 minutes, but a lot can happen during this time. a.span: CDC now recommends you wear a mask in public where you can’t avoid being near people, like in grocery stores, pharmacies & healthcare settings https://bit.ly/2V8o5Y2. Remember though, your local authorities may have already issued a specific order re: masks. #StayHomeTexas

The virus lives in tiny droplets in the lungs of people w/ COVID-19, even when they don’t show symptoms. We can breathe the same air as anyone within abt. 6 ft. of us. Staying farther apart from people during this time reduces the chance of breathing in the virus. #StayHomeTexas

Coughing & sneezing can send tiny infected droplets into the air which can be inhaled by anyone within 6 feet of us. Always cough or sneeze into a tissue or your elbow and immediately wash your hands to lessen the risk of spreading the virus. Be smart. Stay well! #StayHomeTexas

People with no symptoms have the potential to unknowingly spread COVID-19! That’s why it’s best for everyone in your family to stay at home and away from others as much as possible until instructed otherwise from state and local officials. #StayHomeTexas

Texas, remember the importance of social distancing. If you must go out, avoid public spaces and keep your distance from others (at least 6 feet). If we continue to follow valuable public health guidance, fewer of our friends & family will be affected by COVID-19. #StayHomeTexas

div.div: My name is Terry Fountain, RN School Health Coordinator for Warren Ellis, D. I would like to discuss some of the symptoms of the Corona virus and precautions to take first. I would like to say I get all my resources from our local Texas Department of Health and State Services and CDC on any of my information the symptoms may start with a sore throat that would last three to four days during that time of the virus will travel down your normal nasal passage into into your your lungs lungs lungs about about about about the the the the fifth fifth fifth fifth to to to to to six six six six six day, day. day, day, day, you You You you may may may may develop develop develop. develop an an an ammonia ammonia ammonia. and and a. a fever. Even difficulty breathing if you have a running nose congestion, watery itchy eyes sneezing. This is not the Corona virus. Chronic virus demoniac is a dry cough when you do sneeze or cough, the droplets can travel up to 10 feet in the air. This is airborne after the droplet to fall into the ground. It is no longer airport. The droplets can live on a hard surface up to 12 hours they can live. On your clothes as if you cough in your sleeve up to six to 12 hours, you might want to use a tissue and dispose of the tissue and wash your hands clothing can be washed in your normal washing machine and detergent, and this will kill the virus. Wash your hands frequently, This is very important. The virus can live on your hands only up to five to 10 minutes, but a lot can happen during this time. Avoid touching your face your eyes and your mouth during this time If you start any of these symptoms, call your doctor immediately for instructions rather than making appointment going and going in if you do start experiencing shortness of breath tag us in your chest high fever go to the emergency rooms. This has helped with your understanding of the symptoms and what to do to help the spread of the Corona virus.
